          },
          {
            "type": "TextBlock",
            "size": "Large",
            "weight": "Bolder",
            "text": "National reciprocity won't come from the courts \u2014 it has to come from Congress, which returns today",
            "wrap": true,
            "spacing": "Small"
          },
          {
            "type": "TextBlock",
            "text": "The Reload's weekend analysis reads the 8th Cir.'s unanimous Johnson v. Jacobson ruling as foreclosing the judicial path to carry reciprocity: a reciprocity statute \"standing alone, does not regulate arms-bearing conduct.\" The realistic route now runs through H.R. 38 / H.R. 4112, both back on the calendar today.",
            "wrap": true,
            "spacing": "Small"
          },
          {
            "type": "TextBlock",
            "size": "Small",
            "weight": "Bolder",
            "color": "Warning",
            "text": "HOTTEST LEADS",
